  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2014-04-03", 
    "text": "Small Business Fairness in Health Care Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code, as amended by the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (PPACA), to: (1) exempt a small business concern, as defined by the Small Business Act, from the PPACA employer mandate to provide employees with minimum essential health care coverage; and (2) redefine \"full-time employee,\" for purposes of such mandate, as an employee who is employed on average at least 40 (currently, 30) hours a week."
  }, 
